          <p>The Moon is Earth's only natural satellite and the fifth-largest moon in the Solar System. At just 384,400 km away, it's the only celestial body humans have visited. The Moon influences Earth's tides, stabilizes our axial tilt, and has inspired humanity since the dawn of consciousness. It's also the brightest object in our night sky after the Sun.</p>
